the heaviest rainstorm in 90 years 
flooded large sections of this northern mexico state capital on 
sunday killing at least 40 people and leaving more than 5000 
homeless authorities said 
another 30 people were reported missing by the red cross 
the storm which hit saturday night dumped more than 5 inches 
in the area around chihuahua city about 200 miles south of el 
paso texas 
it was still raining in the city of 600000 late sunday and rain 
was forecast to continue for several days 
authorities feared that the chihuahua and chuviscas dams would 
overflow and firemen police and army troops began evacuating 10 
neighborhoods near the two dams on sunday night 
more than 350 homes were destroyed and another 1000 damaged 
said gov fernando baeza melendez who declared an emergency in the 
area around the chihuahua state capital 
about 60 neighborhoods were without running water he said 
dozens of homes in the citys six lowlying neighborhoods either 
collapsed or were swept away by floods and several hundred 
residents had to evacuate their homes chihuahua city police chief 
jesus dover said 
