built in the 1920s and another in 1941 liollio said 
hugo wrenched the roof off and left an inch of water covering 
the floors it wasnt the first disaster the courthouse survived 
an earthquake in 1886 caused heavy damage and toppled its 
chimneys there was talk of razing the building at the time but 
repairs were made 
the original statehouse was built on the site in 1753 under the 
foundation are the original walls of charleston the structure 
