twenty of sundays passengers planned to fly on to california 
and 11 each to texas and michigan myers said 
it was the last scheduled uschartered flight from baghdad 
about 2500 americans have left iraq and kuwait since aug 2 when 
iraq invaded kuwait 
evacuation flights that began earlier this month have brought 
more than 1800 people mostly women and children back to the 
united states the state department said 
iraqi president saddam hussein has refused to allow many men to 
leave and has sent those who have been captured to strategic 
military and industrial sites as a safeguard against attack 
