<TEXT>
king hussein of jordan in a message published 
today said events in the persian gulf threaten to lead to reprise 
of 1914 when the world stumbled into a war it did not want but 
could not stop 
recalling the outbreak 76 years ago of world war i the king 
wrote in the guardian that he believes a war can still be 
prevented but he said if one breaks out it will be impossible to 
limit 
hussein has tried to walk a diplomatic tightrope during the 
crisis he has called for a negotiated solution denouncing the 
iraqi invasion of kuwait but refusing to support the usled 
military buildup standing up to iraq 
in a broadcast message to the american people the king declared 
saturday that his country would never recognize iraqs occupation 
of kuwait 
but he also urged the united states to get out of saudi arabia 
within the shortest period of time 
the guardian said it was publishing husseins remarks as a 
special message his words were published across the top of the 
dailys front page 
it is very disturbing that some believe military action is the 
only solution this is dangerously shortsighted wrote hussein 
the effects of a war against iraq will not be limited to the 
confines of that country 
they will reverberate in every capital throughout the middle 
east they will create the very instability such action was 
designed to prevent 
as for victors and spoils middle east wars have produced 
neither only graveyards for false illusions and the seeds for 
future wars the king wrote 
if the same effort by the world community in the present 
marshalling of military forces the imposition of sanctions and the 
commitment of colossal sums of money were to be applied to a 
political solution i am convinced it could be achieved 
jordan is sandwiched between israel syria iraq and saudi 
arabia 
it has been flooded with refugees from kuwait and iraq since the 
iraqi president saddam hussein ordered his troops into kuwait on 
aug 2 
a unordered embargo on trade with iraq has deprived jordan of 
desperately needed commerce 
in his message king hussein said many who live in the region 
feel helpless to prevent war 
but he wrote i am stubborn enough to believe there is still a 
chance to prevent war i refuse to concede that events cannot be 
brought under control 
the king said a peaceful solution would have to address what he 
called the major underlying causes of the crisis 
he listed these as the dispute between iraq and kuwait the 
imbalance of wealth in the area the unresolved confrontation 
between israel palestine and the arab states and the perilous 
escalation and proliferation of weapons of mass destruction 
saddam has linked a settlement of the crisis to an accord on the 
israelioccupied territories 
to attempt to solve the regions problems by military means 
treats only the symptoms not the causes and would aggravate 
problems the king said 
the area is exhausted from the conflicts and tensions it has 
endured for decades the middle east cannot afford another war 
the world should not impose one on it he said 
i am certain that it is not beyond the ingenuity of the 
leaders of this world to devise a peaceful solution to the crisis 
god help us if they cannot 
