battles with police since the new policy was announced aug 7 
no political party has supported the students position and the 
army has been sent in to maintain law and order in four cities 
schools and colleges have been closed in many towns 
the policy reserves 27 percent of government jobs for people 
from low castes who suffered for centuries under indias strict 
social hierarchy another 225 percent were previously kept aside 
for the most backward castes and native tribes 
singh set a further quota of 5 to 10 percent of jobs for poor 
people irrespective of caste leaving about 40 percent of the 18 
million whitecollar government jobs available on merit alone 
hindus who make up 82 percent of the popluation are divided 
into four castes and hundreds of subcastes discrimination on the 
basis of caste is illegal but in practice the system permeates 
much of indian life especially in the rural areas 
