forward speed by tuesday morning but little change was expected in 
its top sustained wind speed during that time the center reported 
sunday evening the seasons 11th tropical depression dissipated 
in the midatlantic losing its center at about 700 miles 
eastnortheast of the leeward islands 
tropical depressions are redesignated tropical storms if their 
maximum sustained wind speed tops 39 mph storms become hurricanes 
if wind speed reaches 74 mph 
the atlantic hurricane season lasts from june 1 to nov 30 
storms are normally most active in september 
