<TEXT>
in the tradition of the tallmasted clipper ships 
that once raced across the oceans two sailors are taking aim at a 
136yearold record this fall in a san franciscotoboston sweep 
around treacherous cape horn 
skipper richard wilson who has suffered from asthma most of his 
life says hes in it to raise money for lung research and to find 
out what happens when youre cold and wet and tired and scared 
and youve got another 24 hours to go 
wilson and steve pettengill will be shooting for the record of 
76 days 6 hours set by the clipper northern light which roared 
into boston harbor in 1853 loaded with animal hides copper silk 
and fruit 
oct 22 is the tentative departure date for the 14000mile trip 
on the 60foot trimaran great american 
if we dont beat it then the experience will still be 
extraordinary i dont think theres anything else like this in 
sport wilson said we wont stop and there arent any repair 
ships along the way 
