tired there arent any timeouts 
galeforce wind seas over 100 feet and stretches of agonizing 
calm are likely in store for the 2month trip wilson said 
im certain well have some horrendous weather one of the 
great challenges is to just keep going day in and day out he 
said 
to raise money for the cost of the expedition and for the 
american lung association which has named wilson one of its 
superachievers the two will make daily progress reports 
accessible by calling 1900820boat calls cost 350 
several attempts in recent years to beat the times of the old 
speedy skippers are tribute to the continued fascination modernday 
sailors have for the graceful clipper ships that ruled the seas 
from about 1840 to 1870 
the clipper captains were motivated by the financial rewards of 
rushing supplies out to goldrich california or whisking fragrant 
teas and spices back from the orient to get the best price before a 
competitor reached port 
today the lure of the long grueling trips is the challenge of 
