dont wait 
after months of indecision over what path to take the soviet 
parliament voted monday to accept in principle a plan to move to a 
free market economy and reject central planning 
but the journey soviet officials have taken to the market this 
year has been a slow one with reverses and setbacks 
in the spring prime minister nikolai ryzhkov drew up an 
economic reform plan that called for continued central planning a 
strong central government and a slow transition to the market but 
it was quickly rejected by the parliament and returned to him for 
