comments during the meeting were not for publication 
kohl becomes chancellor of all germany when the east and west 
unite on oct 3 he stands a good chance of being reelected on 
dec 2 the date of the first allgerman elections in 57 years 
kohl spoke with the ap board of directors for nearly two hours 
at the chancellery 
he released a written statement to the board containing his 
latest views on a united germanys role in world politics and other 
matters 
many of kohls remarks focused on the global responsibilities of 
a united germany and how they mesh with the political integration 
of europe as a whole 
the chancellor expressed deep gratitude to president bush for 
being the first western leader to affirm the germans right to 
unify 
i wish to single out in particular the contribution made by 
the united states of america kohl said 
he also said he and bush are both interested in seeing serious 
economic reform succeed in the soviet union the germans have 
committed themselves to providing large sums of money to help out 
the soviets 
a successful outcome to these reforms serves us all he 
said 
kohl destined to go into the history books as the architect of 
german unity rejected charges by his political rivals that he 
rushed unification to advance his own career he said the east 
germans determined the pace 
kohl said a mammoth challenge lies ahead because the german 
nations followed drastically different paths after their separation 
four decades ago 
germans will have to show great empathy and understanding in 
order to overcome both the physical and the mental divisions 
between us he said 
people in the impoverished east cannot expect us to create 
equal standards of living for them overnight kohl added 
he rebuffed criticism from some us congressmen and officials 
in other nations that the germans dont want serious global 
responsibilities 
the accusations were made after west germany said its 
constitution barred it from sending soldiers to assist the usled 
multinational forces deployed in the persian gulf after iraq 
invaded kuwait on aug 2 
since then west germany has promised a large financial package 
to help in the gulf crisis 
kohl argued that his policies do have global implications 
for example kohl said he is committed to the political union 
of europe 
we are striving for tangible progress towards a common 
external and security policy within the 12nation european 
economic community he said in his statement 
he said a united germany would not seek the leading role in 
europe but intends to live up to our responsibility in europe 
and in the world 
my government will therefore continue to support the 
international efforts to curb iraqs policy of expansion and to 
restore the territorial integrity of kuwait he said 
the unification of germany and its commitments in a changing 
europe will not prompt us to neglect problems in other parts of the 
world kohl said on the contrary german unification will 
release fresh energies 
in the long run germany and europe as a whole will possess 
additional resources for contributing to economic and social 
development in the third world and to the safeguarding of peace 
worldwide he added 
</TEXT>
