susan cantor 
last year american express publicly apologized to safra 
admitting that people acting on its behalf had tried to discredit 
him american express paid 8 million to charities of safras 
choice to make amends 
freeman later retired from the company accepting responsibility 
for mistakes made on my watch 
larry armour an american express spokesman said monday its 
senseless to respond to old news no matter how colorfully someone 
chooses to repackage it 
the journal said american express and safra began to fall out 
soon after robinson decided in 1983 to buy safras genevabased 
trade development bank and combine it with american express bank 
the styles of the two men differed sharply and in 1984 safra 
resigned from the company the split between safra and robinson 
deepened during negotiations on a settlement package and matters 
grew worse as american express bank officials began to suspect that 
safra who was planning to begin another swiss bank in 1988 was 
hiring away american express employees the journal said 
robert smith former chairman of american express bank told the 
journal he told robinson he had hired detectives to follow the 
former american express workers 
smith said he became obsessed with stopping safra the newspaper 
said his anger spread to other company officials especially 
freeman it said 
the company tried in vain to block safras attempt to get a new 
banking license in switzerland in 1987 the newspaper said 
the next year after safra opened his new bank reports appeared 
in newspapers in europe and south america linking safra to the 
mafia nowdeposed panamanian dictator manuel noriega south 
american drug traffickers the cia and the irancontra scandal 
during the course of a libel suit safra filed against a french 
newspaper minute a lawyer for safra found that a life magazine 
article about the mafia had been faxed to minute from american 
express headquarters in new york the journal said 
safras investigators eventually pegged antonio greco an 
elusive businessman with homes in spain and new york city as the 
source of the articles 
greco was an investigator working for american express the 
journal said he also had an arrest record in the united states and 
italy going back to 1962 and had been convicted on charges 
including theft conspiracy and handling stolen goods the 
newspaper said 
the journal said grecos link at american express was susan 
cantor now a senior vice president at american express bank and 
before that an employee in the american express public relations 
office working under harry freeman the journal said 
freeman was convinced that safra wanted to destroy american 
express bank and had been collecting rumors about him the journal 
said 
at first freeman used ms cantor a former abc news employee 
to gather information on safra but her task evolved to spreading 
rumors and negative news stories about him the newspaper said 
in a statement to the journal ms cantor said she never 
intended or sought to disseminate false information concerning 
edmond safra to anyone and i never instructed asked or engaged 
anyone to spread such information 
the journal said it interviewed dozens of people for the story 
including private detectives and 15 current and former american 
express executives 
