david cowper sailed into the 
river tyne on monday to end a fouryear aroundtheworld voyage 
that included the first solo navigation of the northwest passage 
the 48yearold british surveyor was greeted by a flotilla of 
small craft a band playing rule britannia and a flagwaving crowd 
as his converted former lifeboat moored in newcastle upon tyne on 
englands northeast coast 
cowper holds three records in the guinness book of records 1990 
for previous circumnavigations of the globe a guinness spokeswoman 
said the publisher was awaiting information on his latest trip to 
see if there would be a new record 
cowpers 30000mile journey in the 42foot converted lifeboat 
mabel e holland took more than 50 months making it the slowest of 
his four lone circumnavigations since 1979 
he opted to reach the pacific via the frozen waters of the 
2200mile northwest passage around the arctic coasts of canada and 
alaska but was stopped three times by the winter 
it has been a most rousing welcome which gave me quite a lump 
in my throat i am most relieved to get the boat back at times i 
feared she wouldnt make it he said 
despite facing numerous dangers cowper hinted his taste for 
epic travel had not been satisfied but he said he was keeping his 
next venture a secret in case anyone else beats him to it 
