a news story raising questions about clinical 
trials that led to widespread use of the antiaids drugs azt 
touched off a flap here monday with one activist calling for a 
federal probe 
the miami heralds tropic magazine published a story sunday on 
the role of dr margaret fischl a prominent researcher who helps 
run the university of miami aids program in the 1987 study that 
brought azt to prominence 
the article quoted some researchers as criticizing the methods 
used in the study questioning the accuracy of the figures and 
suggesting that azts effectiveness was overrated by the doctor 
we demand a suspension of her official activities and a 
complete investigation of her and her involvement with burroughs 
wellcome activist bob kunst director of miamibased cure aids 
now said monday this is just a monstrous conspiracy openly 
fraudulently misleading the public on azt 
kunst noted ms fischl sits on the 10member aids clinical 
trials group which directs the governments 100 million research 
effort and said he has written congress asking for an 
investigation 
he said his group along with many others aidsvictim advocates 
has not promoted azt use for several years saying the benefits 
appear to disappear quickly and that side effects are deadly 
ms fischl has connections with the british company making azt 
burroughs wellcome which chose her to run the clinical trials 
here the newspaper said 
ms fischl denied any impropriety in the study or her relations 
with burroughs wellcome 
i do not own stock in pharmaceutical companies she said 
i have never gotten a kickback from burroughs wellcome if 
thats the terminology 
