<TEXT>
here at a glance is a portrait of 
the united germany that will be created oct 3 
 
the land germany will cover 137743 square miles more than 
half the size of texas it combines west germanys 95975 square 
miles with 41768 square miles of east german territory it is 
bordered to the north by denmark and the north and baltic seas by 
the oderneisse river poland czechoslovakia and austria in the 
east by austria switzerland and france to the south and france 
luxembourg belgium and the netherlands to the west 
 
the people germany will have at least 776 million people 61 
million from west germany plus 166 million in east germany 
berlin with 3 million residents is the largest city and its 
capital as stated in the treaty uniting the germanys bonn will be 
the interim seat of government the allgerman parliament to be 
elected dec 2 will decide if the seat of government stays in bonn 
or moves to berlin 
 
economy germany will consist of the most powerful economy of 
western europe and the most powerful of the east bloc 
restructuring east germanys economy to bring it to western 
standards may cost 775 billion unemployment in what is now east 
germany could reach 2 million as formerly statesubsidized firms go 
bankrupt germany has pledged to pay more than 7 billion to the 
soviet union to pay for the withdrawal of the red army from east 
german territory 
 
government germany will be a federal democracy run by 
chancellor helmut kohl vicechancellor and foreign minister 
hansdietrich genscher and president richard von weizsaecker the 
three now hold those posts in west germany 
 
history east germany and west germany were founded in 1949 
after the victorious world war ii allies divided germany west 
germany makes up the german territory occupied by the united 
states france and britain east germany is composed of territory 
occupied by the soviet union 
germany was first united in 1871 under kaiser wilhelm i the 
weimar republic replaced the imperial government at the end of 
world war i nazi dictator adolf hitler replaced the parliamentary 
government in 1933 and ruled until his defeat in 1945 
</TEXT>
