<DOCNO> AP900924-0244 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
but sturges insisted directors were princes of the blood 
the ones who were really in charge by 1939 he was so anxious for 
a chance to direct he offered to accept a salary of 1 his 
screenplays usually brought him 30000 or more if he could make a 
film of down went mcginty a political satire he had written 
several years before paramount gave in even upping his pay to 
10 
i saved my strength i treated myself like an egg wrote 
sturges who gave up drinking and smoking in preparation for the 
film and as a result of this totally regular and totally 
unaccustomed manner of living on the 14th day of shooting i was 
rewarded with pneumonia 
sturges was convinced he had blown it but paramount executives 
were so happy with the scenes he had filmed so far they sent a 
messenger to the directors hospital bed to inform him they would 
wait indefinitely for his recovery 
my fever slid down like a monkey on a flagpole and i was back 
on the set in 10 days sturges wrote 
the great mcginty as it was eventually called was a hit 
and earned sturges an academy award in 1940 for the new category of 
best original screenplay and thanks to sturges frustrated writers 
such as john huston and billy wilder also were allowed to make 
films and became great directors themselves 
sturges made christmas in july sullivans travels 
the lady eve the palm beach story the miracle of 
morgans creek and hail the conquering hero during the next 
four years they are among the wittiest movies ever made and are 
included in a current film forum retrospective in new york 
deception or mistaken identity was often a theme in sturges 
movies in the lady eve barbara stanwyck plays a cardsharp 
then a phony british heiress eddie bracken is wrongly thought to 
be a war hero in conquering hero and dick powell falsely 
believes he has won a contest for writing a coffee slogan in 
christmas in july 
sturges a tall powerfully built man with wavy black hair and a 
thin mustache filmed in the afternoon played host at his 
nightclub in the evening and then wrote until the early morning he 
rarely knew where the story would go once he started and began 
filming morgans creek with just 10 pages of dialogue 
he loved working with mccrae stanwyck and claudette colbert 
but also cultivated a stock company of such motley mountebanks as 
the fumbling raymond walburn the eccentric jimmy conlin and the 
cranky william demarest who had featured parts in morgans 
creek and conquering hero 
but in 1943 after completing conquering hero sturges had a 
falling out with paramount and left to form a film company with the 
reclusive billionare howard hughes 
it was a disaster sturges made the poorly regarded the sin of 
harold diddlebock which hughes soon pulled from circulation and 
the partnership dissolved 
sturges never recovered unfaithfully yours released by fox 
in 1948 did poorly at the box office despite considerable 
publicity and the beautiful blonde from bashful bend fared 
even worse the following year 
unable to catch on with any of the studios sturges spent the 
last decade of his life watching deal after deal fall through 
reduced to minor acting roles and assisting on screenplays 
to sandy sturges his fatal heart attack in august 1959 just 20 
minutes after he had completed his autobiography still doesnt 
make sense he had three deals in the works and had been assured by 
a doctor three months earlier that he was in perfect health and 
could expect to live another 25 years 
he felt confident enough to even joke about his age wanting to 
call his book the events leading up to my death and likening 
his 60th birthday to being a passenger at an ainport but not having 
a flight arranged 
