she had used that idea to guide her horse over obstructions by 
throwing a precise mental image of the movement in front of her and 
following it 
to project the voice the chest must be released out and up 
the posture of anyone who has been successful curtin says 
teaching that to students in the 1970s as a professor at yale 
university was nearly impossible she says 
to stand up straight meant that you were with all the 
conservatives and the warmongers you were for big money she 
says so everyone slunk down the posture was really casual 
curtin started teaching at tanglewood 26 years ago at the peak 
of a performing career that took her to the worlds leading stages 
new yorks metropolitan milans la scala and the vienna 
staatsoper 
on teaching singers fiendishly difficult 20th century music 
curtin quotes olga averino the russianborn soprano who was her 
teacher 
darling so simple says the west virginia native speaking 
with a heavy slavic accent its just like teaching a rabbit how 
to play a drum you just do it over and over and over 
curtin stopped performing at the age of 61 about a decade later 
than most sopranos by that time she had been appointed dean of 
the boston university school for the arts 
the major problem with young singers today she says is that 
theyre often welltrained poodles a homogenized product 
of coaches who tell them by rote what to do 
meanwhile she tells her students i want you to be smart i 
want you to be your own artist i dont want you to be a dumb 
musician 
the main quality of teaching is sharing she says quoting 
thornton wilders novel the ides of march in which caesar 
tells cleopatra that theres nothing so exhilarating as teaching 
to a young and eager mind what its taken you 20 years of drudgery 
to discover 
when shes teaching she says the minute the music turns on 
somehow my channels are open the thing that is emotion that is 
music is running through the center of my body and out out out 
a masterful teacher turns out people who do it better than he 
does and i would like to be that 
she started practicing to be that at age 9 in west virginia 
i took dancing lessons and my very dearest friend did not 
she says so i would come home from my lesson and teach it all 
to her and that was so much fun 
almost six decades after that first attempt at teaching her 
former student baritone sanford sylvan says curtin is his 
artistic motherthe wind beneath my wings 
