<TEXT>
the persian gulf crisis has given 
new life to brazils program to run its vehicles on pure sugarcane 
alcohol instead of gasoline 
shortages of the sugarcane fuel which has high production 
costs and an abundance of inexpensive foreign oil had turned 
brazilians off to alcohol 
but as oil prices have risen beyond 34 a barrel as a result of 
iraqs takeover of kuwait critics are taking another look one of 
the worlds leading alternative fuel programs called proalcohol 
here 
the program is not finished president fernando collor de 
mello told delegates attending a sugarcane energy meeting shortly 
after iraqs aug 2 invasion with the crisis in the gulf the 
strategic importance of proalcohol also increases 
general motors and autolatina a production consortium that 
includes ford and volkswagen announced an immediate 11 percent 
increase in production of cars able to run on alcohol fuel to meet 
a rise in demand 
the country was the victim of an optical illusion that oil 
would be eternally cheap and plentiful julio maria borges 
production director of copersucar brazils largest alcohol 
cooperative said in an interview 
the resurrection of proalcohol is good news for owners of 
brazils 45 million alcohol cars onethird of the nations 
vehicles who believed the clean weetsmelling fuel was the 
energy of the future 
the program began in response to the opec oil shock of 1973 
brazil which imported 80 percent of its petroleum saw its oil 
bill soar from 600 million to 2 billion in 1974 or onefourth of 
total imports 
alcohol seemed like the solution to dependency on foreign oil 
its made from sugar cane a renewable source that grows abundantly 
here and it fit in well with the national security concerns of 
the military governments that ran brazil from 196485 
few mentioned the risks alcohol was untested on a wide scale 
anywhere in the world it gave poor mileage and cost more than 40 
a barrel to make 
but brazil riding the euphoria of its fuel idea was undaunted 
at sinking billions of dollars in a longterm project 
in 1975 its first year proalcohol produced alcohol that mixed 
with gasoline to make gasohol 
in 1979 2271 cars were built and sold that ran solely on pure 
alcohol 
but there were bugs in the early models they wouldnt start on 
cold mornings few in this mostly tropical country but not unknown 
in the southeast and the alcohol corroded metal carburators and 
fuel tanks automakers eventually devised minigas tanks for cold 
starts and anticorrosion coatings 
to compensate for poor mileage the government made alcohol 35 
percent cheaper than gasoline and offered tax breaks on alcohol 
cars it promoted the program with the slogan alcohol cars 
someday youll own one 
the response was overwhelming sales of the new cars rose to 38 
percent of the market in 1982 and 88 percent the next year 
in 1985 the peak for alcohol cars 96 of every 100 cars sold 
were alcoholpowered pumps bearing the green a for alcohol 
sprouted in service stations across this country of 150 million 
residents 
but things began to go wrong for proalcohol 
oil prices leveled off then fell alcohol still 40 a barrel 
began to be too expensive 
worse the government couldnt raise the pump price of alcohol 
without also raising gasoline the spiral of fuel prices helped 
pushed annual inflation up to three digits then four 
farmers encouraged by subsidies replaced food crops with sugar 
cane the government had to import food adding to its 117 billion 
foreign debt highest in the developing world 
in a final irony brazil discovered major offshore oil reserves 
of its own the countrys foreign oil dependency fell under 50 
percent 
critics claimed brazils net energy gain with alcohol was 
negligible because trucks tractors and harvesters on cane 
plantations ran on cheap diesel fuel 
i myself was a critic collor said i shared doubts about 
the high cost of production and deficiency of supply 
in 1989 high sugar prices on the international market led many 
cane growers to make sugar instead of alcohol suddenly there 
wasnt enough alcohol fuel 
long lines formed at service stations and motorists pushing 
alcohol cars that had run out of fuel became a common sight 
popular tv gameshow host fausto silva poked fun at the 
proalcohol slogan joking on his weekly program alcohol cars 
someday youll push one 
the government was forced to import alcohol it cut the price 
advantage of alcohol over gasoline to 25 percent added gasoline to 
alcohol and reduced the alcohol content in gasohol in most cities 
only sao paulo brazils most populous city kept a higher 
alcohol mix to reduce air pollution the cane fuel produces half 
the carbon monoxide of gasoline and no harmful hydrocarbons 
sales of alcohol cars plummeted below 5 percent of the market in 
july 
now while alcohol has gotten a reprive because of the gulf 
crisis jacy mendonca president of the national auto makers 
association warned it might not be lasting or significant 
added borges of copersucar the problem is that diesel fuel is 
very cheap less than half the price of gasoline and thats a 
very strong incentive to use it in every vehicle you can 
collor who took office in march abolished the governments 
sugar and alcohol institute widely seen as inefficient and 
corrupt to guarantee the alcohol supply cane producers must now 
get government permission to export 
proalcohol also will get funds for research to attain full 
economic viability he said 
society should have a positive view of proalcohol collor 
said it is a successful project that cannot be tampered with 
