global corporations will help each other stop those multinational 
companies from exploiting workers nation by nation maitland 
said 
umw president richard trumka said he signed the agreement so 
our two countries never scab on one another ever in the future 
the practical effect of the agreement however is not clear 
because us labor law prohibits secondary boycotts against 
companies because of a strike against a different operation 
the convention which began sept 17 ends tuesday with 
addresses by us labor secretary elizabeth dole and united 
steelworkers union president lynn williams 
